# Day 04 - HTTP Methods and HTTP Headers

## Objective

To understand how HTTP requests work, different HTTP methods, and how browsers communicate with web servers.

---

# Practical 1: HTTP Methods using cURL

## GET Request

URL:

https://httpbin.org/get

Purpose:
Retrieve information from the server.

Observation:
The server returned request information in JSON format.

---

## POST Request

Command

```cmd
curl -X POST https://httpbin.org/post
```

Purpose:
Send data to the server.

Observation:
The server accepted the POST request.

---

## POST Request with Data

Command

```cmd
curl -X POST https://httpbin.org/post -d "name=Sakshi"
```

Observation:
The server received the value:

```
name = Sakshi
```

---

## PUT Request

Command

```cmd
curl -X PUT https://httpbin.org/put
```

Purpose:
Replace an existing resource.

Observation:
The server successfully processed the request.

---

## PATCH Request

Command

```cmd
curl -X PATCH https://httpbin.org/patch
```

Purpose:
Update part of an existing resource.

Observation:
The server successfully processed the request.

---

## DELETE Request

Command

```cmd
curl -X DELETE https://httpbin.org/delete
```

Purpose:
Delete a resource.

Observation:
The server successfully processed the request.

---

# HTTP Methods Summary

| Method | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| GET | Retrieve data |
| POST | Submit data |
| PUT | Replace existing data |
| PATCH | Partially update existing data |
| DELETE | Delete data |

